		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Theory of the firm</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p>The <b>theory of the firm</b> consists of a number of <a href="/wiki/Economic_theory" title="Economic theory" class="mw-redirect">economic theories</a> which describe the nature of the firm, <a href="/wiki/Company_(law)" title="Company (law)" class="mw-redirect">company</a>, or <a href="/wiki/Corporation" title="Corporation">corporation</a>, including its existence, its behaviour, and its relationship with the <a href="/wiki/Market" title="Market">market</a>.</p>
